<span id="freeTextContainer12493192592571995634">What can one say about Asimov that he didn&apos;t say about himself.... over and over and over again? Why, nothing. He was a genius and an egoist and a great man and the face of the science fiction field for decades. He&apos;s suffered some posthumous criticism because of his attitudes that are now seen as sexist, but I would argue that he was very much a product of his times and shouldn&apos;t be judged by contemporary standards. His writings are always fascinating, the story of his life no less so than his f</span>
  <span id="freeText12493192592571995634" style="display:none">What can one say about Asimov that he didn't say about himself.... over and over and over again? Why, nothing. He was a genius and an egoist and a great man and the face of the science fiction field for decades. He's suffered some posthumous criticism because of his attitudes that are now seen as sexist, but I would argue that he was very much a product of his times and shouldn't be judged by contemporary standards. His writings are always fascinating, the story of his life no less so than his fiction. </span>
